 can be used to cancel the source, which will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cause the source to trigger, reporting the current condition (which","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is likely 0 unless cancellation happened at the same time as a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition change). You can check for this in the callback using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_cancellable_is_cancelled()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"socket"},{"type":"text","text":" has a timeout set, and it is reached before "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"condition"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"occurs, the source will then trigger anyway, reporting [in_](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/in_ or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[out](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/out depending on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"condition"},{"text":". However, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"socket"},{"type":"text","text":" will have been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"marked as having had a timeout, and so the next "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" I\/O method"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you call will then fail with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"timedOut","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a [Source](\/\/documentation\/glib\/source that can be attached to a [MainContext](\/\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext to monitor","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the availability of the specified "},{"code":"condition","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on the socket. The [Source](\/\/documentation\/glib\/source"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"